  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Travel Retail Manager",
  "description": "<p>Maison 21G is redefining luxury fragrance with creativity, craftsmanship, and conscious innovation and we’re looking for a dynamic <strong>Travel Retail Manager (B2C)</strong> to lead our multi-channel retail business across the Asia-Pacific region.<br /></p><p>The ideal candidate will oversee <strong>Travel Retail, Distributors, E-commerce,</strong> and our <strong>Singapore boutiques,</strong> ensuring commercial growth, operational excellence, and brand consistency across every touchpoint. This is a rare opportunity to drive Maison 21G’s expansion across Asia while preserving the artistry that defines our Maison.<br /></p><p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Lead & Unify Channels:</strong> Oversee Travel Retail (Singapore, Malaysia, HK, Macau, Australia, Thailand), Distributors (Korea), E-commerce, and Singapore boutiques.</li><li><strong>Drive Performance:</strong> Manage sell-in / sell-out activities, client relationships, and negotiations while optimizing visual merchandising and retail marketing.</li><li><strong>Own the Numbers:</strong> Take full P&L responsibility from sales and margins to operating expenses ensuring growth and profitability across markets.</li><li><strong>Inspire Teams:</strong> Motivate and align multicultural Beauty Advisor teams, fostering collaboration between marketing, training, operations, and supply chain.</li><li><strong>Grow Strategically:</strong> Identify new business opportunities in department stores and Travel Retail (including Thailand and Malaysia), and launch creative activations that elevate customer engagement.</li></ul><p><strong>Who You Are</strong></p><ul><li>3-5 years of commercial leadership in <strong>luxury, beauty, or fragrance retail</strong> — ideally with Travel Retail experience.</li><li>A proven track record in <strong>multi-channel sales and P&L management.</strong></li><li>A <strong>charismatic, hands-on leader</strong> who blends operational expertise and analytical precision with creative vision.</li><li>Agile, entrepreneurial, and passionate about innovation in luxury retail.</li><li>Fluent in <strong>English;</strong> proficiency in <strong>Mandarin or another Asian language</strong> is a plus.</li></ul>",
